<div class="page-header">
	<h1>How To Use</h1>
</div>

<p>
	This page is intended as a quick-start guide. For way more detailed information about the script - especially the
	main config object, see the <a href="#docs" class="selectPage">Docs</a> page.
</p>

<ol>
	<li>
		In your page, include the d3.js, jquery and d3pie libs. These can be placed anywhere.
		<pre class="prettyprint language-html">&lt;script src="//cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/d3/3.4.4/d3.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script src="//ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.11.0/jquery.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script src="d3pie.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
</pre>
		This code references the CDN hosted versions of d3 and jQuery - but you can always just download them and
		install them on your own server. You will need to <a href="#download" class="selectPage">download d3pie.min.js</a>
		and host that yourself.
	</li>

	<li>
		Create an element in the page where you want the pie chart to appear. You don't need to give the element
		any particular class or ID, but generally an ID is the simplest way to do it.
		<pre class="prettyprint language-html">&lt;div id="myPie"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</pre>
	</li>

	<li>
		Add
		<script>
			var pie = new d3pie("mypie", { });
		</script>

		The second parameter is the config object. The next section explains that.
	</li>
</ol>

